<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-573-191  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 573 191.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Nov 1990 v15 n12 p165(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fast new systems from NeXT. (Hardware Review) (includes relatedarticle on NextStep 2.0 and 2.0 Extended operating system)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Baran, Nick; Linderholm, Owen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>NeXT Inc's workstation product line now features the new Motorola68040 microprocessor running at 25MHz and a MS-DOS compatible2.88Mbyte floppy disk drive.andP;  The Nextstation is a pizza-box stylemachine that comes standard with 8Mbytes of memory, a 105Mbytehard disk drive, and the 2.88Mbyte floppy disk drive.andP;  The systemcosts $4,995 with the 17-inch monochrome MegaPixel display.andP;  The$7,995 Nextcube offers similar specifications with space for onehalf-height and one full-height storage device, but the on-boardmemory can be expanded to 64Mbytes.andP;  The 340Mbyte drive optionretails at $9,995.andP;  The Nextstation Color offers the sameslim-case style and specifications as the Nextstation but supports16-bit color, and comes standard with 12Mbytes of RAM and 2Mbytesof video memory.andP;  A 12Mbyte system with color display is priced at$7,995.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   NeXT Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   NeXT NeXTstation (Workstation)NeXT NeXTcube (Workstation)NeXT NeXTstation Color (Workstation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationWorkstationsComputer industry.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>